HEADWORD: Intransigent
<hw>In*trans"i*gent</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>intransigeant</ets> (cf. Sp. <ets>intransigente</ets>); pref.
<ets>in-</ets> not + L. <ets>transigere</ets> to come to an agreement;
<ets>trans</ets> across + <ets>agere</ets> to lead, act.]</ety>
<def>Refusing compromise; uncompromising; inflexible;
irreconcilable.</def> <rj><au>Lond. Sat. Rev.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

